          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The samples were based at 13m from the neutron",
                " source in the total cross section experiment.",
                ".The capture samples were placed inside the liquid",
                " scintillator tank."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight method, transmission",
                " measurements. For specific details of the experiments,",
                " regarding detector calibration, background reduction,",
                " beam filtering etc. See Gayther's private",
                " communication."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " NE110 plastic scintillator coupled to a low",
                " noise photomultiplier (RCA type 4522) at flight",
                " paths 50 and 100 m used in the total cross-section",
                " measurement.",
                ".A large liquid scintillator with an efficiency of",
                " nearly 100% (230 l of NE211), viewed by 12",
                " photomultipliers, was used in the capture measurement.",
                " A detailed description is given in Gayther's private",
                " communication. It was placed at 97.5m flight path."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MOXR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Moxon-Rae detector was used at 32m flight",
                " path in the low energy part of the capture",
                " measurement. Its nominal TOF-resolution was 5 ns/m."
              ]
            }
          ],
